Usage: pmiostat [options]

General options:
  -A TIME, --align=TIME align sample times on natural boundaries
  -a FILE, --archive=FILE
                        metrics source is a PCP log archive
  -G method, --aggregate=method
                        aggregate values for devices matching -R regex using 'method' (sum, avg, min or max)
  -h HOST, --host=HOST  metrics source is PMCD on host
  -O TIME, --origin=TIME
                        initial sample time within the time window
  -P N, --precision=N   N digits after the decimal separator
  -R pattern, --regex=pattern
                        only report for devices names matching pattern, e.g. 'sd[a-zA-Z]+'. See also -G.
  -S TIME, --start=TIME start of the time window
  -s N, --samples=N     terminate after this many samples
  -T TIME, --finish=TIME
                        end of the time window
  -t DELTA, --interval=DELTA
                        sampling interval
  -u, --no-interpolation
                        disable interpolation mode with archives
  -V, --version         display version number and exit
  -Z TZ, --timezone=TZ  set reporting timezone
  -z, --hostzone        set reporting timezone to local time of metrics source
  -?, --help            show this usage message and exit

Extended options:
  -x LIST               comma separated extended options: [[dm],[t],[h],[noidle]]
		dm	show device-mapper statistics (default is sd devices)
		t	precede every line with a timestamp in ctime format
		h	suppress headings
		noidle	do not display idle devices
